o resonate since its publication in 1952, Form and Event anticipates the work of such French and Italian post-war thinkers as Gilles Deleuze, Alain Badiou, Roberto Esposito, and Giorgio Agamben.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aPhilosophy, Ancient. 4aLiterary Studies. 4aPhilosophy & Theory. 4aPolitical Science. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh  aAchilles.  aEvent.  aForm.  aHeidegger.  aOdysseus.  aPhenomenology.1 aCampbell, Timothy C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiano, Carlo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLezra, Jacques, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurtas, Lia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311072271040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780823287949?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823287949423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780823287949/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070482-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-072271-0  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEB